A man is critically injured after a light motor vehicle and a bus collided on Paul Kruger Street in Pretoria, on Monday morning.ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said a 32-year-old man was found trapped inside the light motor vehicle, he sustained numerous injuries and was in a critical condition.&#8220;Rescue services had to use the jaws-of-life equipment to free the man from the vehicle.&#8220;Once freed, paramedics treated the man and provided him with several advanced life support interventions. He was thereafter transported to Steve Biko Hospital for urgent treatment,&#8221; said Meiring.The driver of the bus was treated and transported to the hospital by another service.The cause of the collision is being investigated by the local authorities.